Father Józef Witko: I saw Jesus in a white robe
He is charismatic.
At Mass celebrated by him, St. Crowds flock to deliverance and healing.
He was a teenager when inexplicable things began to happen in his life.
Today, through the Franciscan, others experience it.
The Holy Mass celebrated by Father Witko Crowds flock to deliverance and healing
Once, the parents of a 7-month-old child who had a 7.5 mm hole in his heart came to him.
It was supposed to be operated on.
Father Józef Witko prayed over him.
The same day, the boy was taken to the hospital for surgery.
The astonished doctors said: &quot;Operation is not needed, the defect is only 1.5 mm.&quot;
Parents cried with happiness.
After another prayer of the Franciscan, the hole disappeared completely.
The priest began to experience the unusual actions of the Creator as a teenager.
In his dreams, souls in purgatory came to him asking for help.
I was woken up at night and urged to pray for the dead and those who were dying at the moment,” he recalls.
He also experienced the presence of an evil spirit.
And he had a vision of what happens to a man who commits a mortal sin.
“My body started to change.
I lost my human features and started to look like an animal,” he says.
An invisible force lifted him up, unable to utter a voice.
He felt lost.
Then God showed him help.
&quot;Immersed in the waters of the river symbolizing holy baptism, I was freed and returned to human form...&quot;, he says.
He told no one about these strange experiences.
A vocation was ripening in him.
He was 16 when he joined the Franciscans.
In his sermons, he wanted to talk about more than just Jesus.
He wanted people to experience Him alive.
Members of the charismatic community of Renewal in the Holy Spirit
Many people who hope to get rid of the disease participate in healing masses celebrated by Father Witko.
The priest emphasizes, however, that their main goal is spiritual healing, not bodily.
