Make sure you wash your hands properly
We all know that they need to be washed (e.g. after coming home or before a meal).
But not everyone knows that to actually get rid of germs, you have to do it the right way.
This is especially important now that autumn infections are approaching.
It takes at least 30-40 seconds for washing to sufficiently remove dangerous bacteria and viruses from our hands
And yet most of us wash them less!
All you need is warm water and ordinary soap - it&#39;s not true that it has to be antibacterial (many doctors even advise against it).
When washing, we rub not only the bottoms and tops of the hands, but also: fingertips (joined or individually) - rub them with circular movements on the inside of the other hand, spaces between the fingers (interlace hands, rubbing fingers against each other), thumbs - each thumb is covered with the other hand and in such an embrace we turn it to the right and left for a moment.
In an emergency (when you cannot wash your hands), you should wipe your hands with a wet tissue and then use an antibacterial gel (in drugstores, from PLN 5).
After using a public toilet, do not touch door handles or doors with clean hands (recommendation of the Chief Sanitary Inspectorate).
Open them with a paper towel.
Iranian President Says He Rejected U.S. Talks, Donald Trump Denies
Tehran did not start talks with the American side during the UN General Assembly in New York, despite the American offer to lift sanctions, Iranian President Hassan Rouhani said on Friday.
US President Donald Trump commented that it was the Iranian side that asked for the lifting of restrictions, which he did not agree to.
According to Iranian President Hassan Rouhani, the Americans have offered to lift all sanctions on Tehran in exchange for negotiations on a new international agreement.
It would regulate both Iran&#39;s nuclear program and its ballistic missile program.
Rouhani: Iran will not enter talks under maximum pressure
Iran&#39;s president said he refused to hold the talks because of the &quot;toxic atmosphere&quot;.
He stated that he met with American diplomats because he had succumbed to the urgings of France, Germany and Great Britain.
He stressed, however, that Iran would not enter into talks in an atmosphere of &quot;maximum pressure&quot;.
&quot;And even if we want to negotiate with the Americans in a 5+1 format, no one can predict what the end result will be,&quot; Rouhani said.
The day before, the Iranian leader said that he did not rule out talks with the US, and accused the European parties to the nuclear deal of favoring US sanctions on Iran.
He added that the sanctions imposed on Iran after the U.S. withdrawal from the nuclear deal &quot;are a precondition that does not allow&quot; dialogue to be established.
If we can lift that precondition and if America lifts the sanctions and maximum pressure, then of course we can talk to America,&quot; he declared.
He added that he did not rule out a meeting with US President Donald Trump, despite the fact that he did not agree to such a conversation last week during the UN General Assembly.
Trump: &#39;Iran asked, I said no&#39;
Donald Trump tweeted that he was the one who rejected the request from the Iranian side.
“Iran wanted me to lift the sanctions on them so we could meet.
Of course I said &quot;no!&quot; tweeted the US president.
Tension with a nuclear deal in the background
France, Germany and the UK are trying to ease tensions between Washington and Tehran in order to salvage the 2015 Iran deal they were signatories to in some form.
It stated that in return for the lifting of economic sanctions, Iran would abandon its nuclear weapons program and submit its nuclear sector to the control of the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA).
Since the U.S. withdrawal from the agreement in May 2015, the remaining signatories have repeatedly confirmed that they want to keep the agreement in force.
So far nothing has come of it.
Washington uses maximum pressure tactics on Iran, and the sanctions include a full embargo on Iranian oil.
Tehran has announced that if it does not receive permission to export the oil, it will reduce its obligations under the agreement every 60 days.
