The power of Oława jumps.
The title of the report from the amateur sports competition, played on Sunday afternoon, September 15 at the hippodrome at Oleandry Street in Oława, may be misleading for some.
The road to true power is long, but this is the name used to describe one of the types of horse competition...
The power of jumping competition consists in overcoming by the rider and the horse higher and higher obstacles, which in the most prestigious international competitions exceed even two meters.
It is worth adding here that the long-term and still unbeaten world record, set in 1949 by the Chilean Albert Larraguibel, on the horse &quot;Huaso&quot;, is 247 cm.
Of course, no one jumped so high in Oława, but the result of the best local amazons at the level of 135 cm is also not the worst...
The competition organized by the tireless Jan Sienkiewicz and other activists of JKS &quot;W saddle&quot;, was a show part of the &quot;Rainbow Riding Competition&quot; held there a little earlier, about which we write more in this issue of the newspaper, on page 22.
Eight horse riders, training horse riding in JKS in Oława, joined the competition.
Four competed on ponies and four on large horses.
In the first group, Nikola Szołdra, riding on the crazy &quot;Sprinter&quot;, did the best job.
This small but very dynamic steed started by overcoming obstacles set at a height of 40 cm, and ended only at the station with the upper beam 125 cm from the ground.
However, he did not give up easily and only after three consecutive refusals was he removed from further competition by the competition jury.
The second place in pony jumping was taken by Amelia Pawlak, riding &quot;Fama&quot;, and the third place was taken by Lena Boruń on &quot;Harmider&quot;.
The youngest participant of the tournament - Inga Aksman - fought ambitiously, galloping and jumping over obstacles on a small mare &quot;Carmen&quot;.
Even greater emotions accompanied the starting amazons and spectators during the competition with the participation of large horses.
Paulina Szewczyk, riding &quot;Declaration&quot; and Anastazja Abramenko, riding &quot;Lotka&quot;, had some dangerous-looking falls.
Fortunately, apart from minor bruises, neither the amazons nor the horses were hurt, so they continued to participate in the competition.
Weronika Łuczkiewicz, who was riding her, had a lot of problems with introducing the young mare &quot;Wineta&quot; to the showcourse.
Either the trainer&#39;s assistance was needed, or another pairing horse, followed by a bit crazy &quot;Wineta&quot;.
After passing the obstacle, she also went down the parkour at full gallop, so sometimes it got dangerous in the boxes and on the warm-up area. “Everything is under control!”, Jan Sienkiewicz reassured the somewhat frightened spectators, especially the youngest ones.
From the beginning of the competition for large horses, Marta Masalska, riding the beautifully presented &quot;Whiskey&quot;, was doing great on the arena.
This dignified mare, together with an experienced horsewoman, was the first to jump over 135 cm in the second attempt in the final phase, which was the best result of the competition at that moment.
After a while, however, the same height was also achieved by Paulina Szewczyk on &quot;Declaration&quot;, Weronika Łuczkiewicz on &quot;Wineta&quot; and Anastazja Abramenko on &quot;Lotka&quot;.
Therefore, all these contestants left together to decorate the flo and receive material prizes in the form of equestrian equipment, and finally, together with horse pony amazons, they performed an impressive round of honor to the rhythm of Radecki&#39;s march, ending this interesting and exciting competition.
