The Senate decided on key bills
The Senate adopted, without amendments, the bills on disclosure of the assets of the families of the most important state officials and on the flights of the most important people in the state.
52 senators voted for the amendment to the act on family assets of state officials - without amendments - 14 were against, three abstained from voting.
Thus, the senators decided to reject 12 amendments submitted during Wednesday&#39;s debate by PO senator Sławomir Rybicki.
According to him, the amendments were intended to &quot;civilize&quot; the act and limit the scope of information provided in the declaration on the financial situation of one&#39;s own children, children of the spouse, children adopted in cases where the children remain in a common household with the person obliged to submit the declaration.
The act on disclosure of assets of the families of the most important state officials, drafted by the Prime Minister&#39;s office, was passed by the Sejm on 11 September.
The regulations stipulate that the prime minister, ministers, deputies, members of the European Parliament, senators, presidents of: the Constitutional Tribunal, the Supreme Administrative Court and the Supreme Court, as well as persons heading other state institutions will be obliged to include information on the personal property of spouses, children and dependents in the asset declaration in shared use.
The Senate also did not propose amendments to the law on flights of the most important people in the state.
It regulates which flights have HEAD status and who can be on board government planes along with the most important people in the country.
The Act also specifies who is responsible for keeping the Central Register of Flights.
55 senators were in favor of the bill – without amendments – 12 were against it and four abstained from voting.
According to the act, each flight of the president will be a flight &quot;performed on an official mission&quot;.
In the flights, the president will be able to be accompanied by family members and other persons invited by the president.
On the other hand, the flight in the official mission of the Prime Minister and the Marshals of the Sejm and the Senate will be only a flight &quot;carried out in order to perform tasks directly related to the function performed&quot;.
The Act also specifies the list of persons who may accompany the most important people in the country during the flight.
According to the regulations, members of the delegation - invited deputies, senators, representatives of public authorities and experts - may be on board the aircraft; persons providing technical, medical or organizational support; as well as journalists.
Pursuant to the Act, in the event of doubts related to the flights of the Marshals of the Sejm and the Senate, the head of the Chancellery of the Prime Minister will request clarification.
If such doubts are not clarified within the specified time, the head of the Chancellery of the Prime Minister will be obliged to notify the heads of the Chancelleries of the Sejm or Senate of the impossibility of organizing such a flight.
